The paper discusses a multiround algorithm for distributed data processing systems, specifically for computing the equijoin of n relations. This falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new notion of queries and generalized hypertree decompositions (GHDs) to capture how connected the adjacent cyclic components of the GHDs are, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between communication and the number of rounds, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and distributed systems (cs.Distributed Systems).
